ts=2026-06-12T11:27:15.392Z type=preference scope=summarize-material content="Footer format for summarized lectures: `_X min read (source: Y min)_` where X is summary read time and Y is original source read time." tags=footer,format,summarize
ts=2026-06-12T11:27:16.607Z type=preference scope=opencode content="When user says \"remember\", use memory tools (memory_remember) to store the information rather than just acknowledging it." tags=workflow,memory
ts=2026-06-12T12:19:43.961Z type=preference scope=summarize-material content="It's okay to have summary equal in readtime to the source. Only trim if it's greater than it." tags=readtime,trimming,summarize
ts=2026-06-12T12:39:58.211Z type=preference scope=opencode content="Use `nullptr` (not NULL) in all C++ code. Use `this->` keyword in OOP methods for clarity." tags=cpp,nullptr,this,style
ts=2026-06-12T12:39:59.624Z type=preference scope=dsa-lectures content="Use `nullptr` (not NULL) and `this->` in all OOP C++ lecture code." tags=cpp,nullptr,this,style
ts=2026-06-12T12:57:10.211Z type=preference scope=summarize-material content="Don't remove the `# Course Name - [Lecture|Section|Task|Assignment] N` header from the summary." tags=header,format,summarize
ts=2026-06-12T13:05:46.928Z type=preference scope=dsa-lectures content="Node struct property naming: use `data` (not `info`) for the data member in all node/struct definitions across lectures." tags=naming,node,data
ts=2026-06-12T13:18:15.317Z type=preference scope=summarize-material content="When explaining concepts, use Mermaid flowcharts (Mermaid code blocks do not count toward read time). Only include a flowchart if it adds value; otherwise, skip it." tags=mermaid,flowcharts,format
ts=2026-06-12T16:19:13.283Z type=preference scope=code-style content="When the user provides code snippets to include in summaries, do NOT copy them verbatim. Always refactor to match established conventions: `this->` for member access, `data` (not `info`) for node members, `nullptr` (not NULL), C++11 style (constructors, destructors, templates, `auto`), 2-space indentation in code blocks."
